.TH G15STATS 1 "April 2026" "g15stats 3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
g15stats \- display system statistics on Logitech G15 LCD devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B g15stats
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B g15stats
shows system statistics on Logitech G15 LCD displays through g15daemon.
It supports multiple screens including CPU, memory, swap, network,
temperature, fan, battery, and frequency views.
.PP
Configuration is loaded in this order:
.IP "1." 4
Environment variable
.BR G15STATS_CONFIG_FILE
if set.
.IP "2." 4
User config at
.BR ~/.config/g15stats/g15stats.yaml .
.IP "3." 4
System config at
.BR /etc/g15plugins/g15stats.yaml .
.PP
If both user and system config are missing, g15stats creates a default user
config file at first run.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.BR -d , " --daemon"
Run in background.
.TP
.BR -u , " --unicore"
Show unicore graphs only on CPU screen.
.TP
.BR -i " " iface , " --interface " iface
Monitor network interface
.IR iface .
.TP
.BR -t " " id , " --temperature " id
Force temperature sensor id.
.TP
.BR -gt " " id , " --global-temp " id
Select summary temperature sensor id.
.TP
.BR -f " " id , " --fan " id
Force fan sensor id.
.TP
.BR -nsa , " --net-scale-absolute"
Scale network graphs against highest seen speed.
.TP
.BR -ir , " --info-rotate"
Enable rotating bottom info bar.
.TP
.BR -vc , " --variable-cpu"
Re-detect CPU core count continuously.
.TP
.BR -df , " --disable-freq"
Disable CPU frequency monitoring.
.TP
.BR -r " " seconds , " --refresh " seconds
Set refresh interval (1..300 seconds).
.TP
.BR -o " " path , " --output-file " path
Write LCD frame data to
.I path
instead of sending to g15daemon.
.TP
.BR -D , " --debug"
Enable debug logging to stderr.
.TP
.B --bar-background
Enable bar chart background boxes.
.TP
.B --temp-filter-bypass
Disable temperature moving average filter.
.TP
.BI --cpu2-bar-height " pixels"
Set CPU LOAD2 target bar height (1..33).
.TP
.B --no-screen-overlay
Disable one-refresh overlay after screen changes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/g15stats/g15stats.yaml
User config file.
.TP
.I /etc/g15plugins/g15stats.yaml
System config file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/g15stats/examples/g15stats.yaml.example
Sample configuration.
.SH SYSTEMD USER SERVICE
The package provides a user unit:
.BR g15stats.service .
Enable and start it with:
.PP
.B systemctl --user enable --now g15stats.service
.PP
The unit runs in foreground mode and uses the user config path above.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B G15STATS_CONFIG_FILE
Override config file path.
.TP
.B G15STATS_PAUSE
Override refresh pause used internally.
.TP
.B G15STATS_FORCE_SCREEN
Force initial screen index.
